def: To lay as in a bed; to lay in surrounding matter; to bed; as,to embed a thing in clay, mortar, or sand.
A yellow crystalline substance having a peculiar unpleasantodor, resembling the quinones, and obtained from beechwood tar andcoal tar, as also by the oxidation of xylidine; -- called alsoxyloquinone.
One who mouths; an affected speaker.
A proteid substance (acid albumin) formed from the albuminousmatter of muscle by the action of dilute acids; -- formerly calledmusculin. See Acid albumin, under Albumin.
The quality or state of being slovenly.
A quantity of oats paid by a tenant to a landlord in lieu ofrent. Jacob.
A duty payable to the lord mayor of London by the sellers ofale within the city.
heathy land; land full of heather; moorish or watery land.[prov. Eng.]
Capable of being assigned, allotted, specified, or designated;as, an assignable note or bill; an assignable reason; an assignablequantity.
To answer, as the defendant to the plaintiff's replication.
